         <abstract>
            <p>The greedy algorithm was used to generate sets of positive integers containing no subset of the form $\{x, x + y, x + 2y\}, \{x, x + y, x + 3y\}, \{x, x + 2y, x + 3y\}, \{x, x + 3y, x + 4y\}, \{x, x + 3y, x + 5y\}$, and $\{x, x + y, x + 2y, x + 3y\}$, respectively. All of these sets have peaks of density in roughly geometric progression.</p>
          </abstract>
